      "content": {
        "title": "Glenohumeral Arthritis — Non-Arthroplasty Management — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Degenerative, inflammatory, and post-traumatic glenohumeral arthritis managed conservatively or with joint-preserving surgery.",
        "summary": "Young patients may undergo arthroscopic debridement or interposition. Cuff tear arthropathy requires reverse total shoulder arthroplasty rather than anatomic replacement."
      },
